This paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for melanoma detection in dermoscopic images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) domains. The paper also discusses the interpretability of the models, which is a topic of interest in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) community. Additionally, the paper deals with medical image analysis, which is a subfield of medical informatics (cs.MED). Finally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for interpreting the models, which falls under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) domain.
